  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Finance Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Summary:</strong></u></p><p>We are seeking a skilled Finance Executive to lead and oversee our administrative, personnel and financial operations in Singapore office. The person is responsible to oversee end-to-end financial processes, administration and payroll activities for Singapore office, with a specific focus on managing the documentation, cash flows, invoicing and tax obligations of a company, including the accounting registration of economic movements, the issuing and receiving of invoices, the calculation of VAT, the management of relationships\nwith banks and suppliers and the preparation of accounting documents and the balance sheet. He/she also plays a critical role in overseeing accurate and timely administration of the organization's\npayroll for both direct and temporary employees, managing communication and data management with the third-party agency.<br /><br /><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p><ul><li>Ensure accuracy and completeness of monthly accounting records in SAP and yearly statutory accounts in accordance with local Gaap and Group accounting policies </li><li>Record/Oversee all day-to-day transactions, including accounts payable/receivable, general ledger, fixed assets and bank reconciliations</li><li>Fill out monthly VAT reports</li><li>Assist the external auditors during the annual closing of the financial statements and maintain relationships with tax and payroll authorities and consultants </li><li>Provide analysis and appropriate documentation</li><li>to internal and external parties to ensure compliance with local</li><li>legislation and group requirements</li><li>Prepare monthly management reports and analyze</li><li>variances between actuals, forecasts and budget</li><li>Oversee analytical accounting, budgeting and</li><li>forecasting in coordination with the General Manager</li><li>Process employees payroll calculation and manage CPF contributions and any other statutory submissions</li></ul></p><p><u><strong>Qualifications:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or a related field; CPA preferred.</li><li>Minimum of 3 years of experience in finance management or a similar role.</li><li>Strong knowledge of financial principles, accounting standards, and regulatory compliance.</li><li>Proven track record of financial analysis and strategic planning.</li><li>Excellent communication, and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Advanced proficiency in <strong>SAP,</strong> and Microsoft Excel </li></ul><p><br /></p>",
